Strong balance sheets exceeded those with a weak balance sheet after each of the interest rate increases in 1994, 1999 and 2004, with an average of 5 percentage points.
Companies with large capital revenues as well as low volatility stocks have also exceeded similar companies of lower quality, with an average of 4 (percentual points) and 3 (percentual points) respectively.
The debt will become an important problem.
